  "slug": "mutton-pie",
  "title": "Mutton Pie",
  "subtitle": "Slow-braised mutton shoulder under a rough shortcrust lid, rich with onion and herbs",
  "excerpt": "Mutton is older, fattier, and more flavourful than lamb. Braised shoulder set in a deep dish under a shortcrust pastry lid produces a pie with a depth of flavour that lamb cannot match. It is a cold-weather pie, best made a day ahead.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Traditional British and Scottish. Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136: mutton pie method. F. Marian McNeill, The Scots Kitchen (1929): mutton and vegetable pie. Traditional British and Welsh farmhouse cooking.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mutton",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4nyb0000wkv4zi1f733n"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " needs long, slow cooking to become tender. The shoulder, cut into large chunks, benefits from 2 hours of braising in stock and aromatics. The reward is a sauce that is deeply savoury, and meat that is yielding and rich in a way that lamb shoulder rarely achieves.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "lid-only pie",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpdr4nyy0001wkv4nfdwk29k"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": the filling goes into the dish and the pastry sits on top, pressed onto the rim. It is easier to execute than a fully lined pie and the base requires no separate cooking.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
